Here is a Python snippet to estimate the decline in per capita food production using hypothetical data for wheat, pork, and beef production in 1840 and 1860:

python
# Hypothetical data (in millions of units)
production_1840 = {'wheat': 100, 'pork': 50, 'beef': 30}
production_1860 = {'wheat': 80, 'pork': 40, 'beef': 20}
population_1840 = 17.1  # in millions
population_1860 = 31.4  # in millions

# Calculate per capita production for 1840 and 1860
per_capita_1840 = {k: v / population_1840 for k, v in production_1840.items()}
per_capita_1860 = {k: v / population_1860 for k, v in production_1860.items()}

# Calculate the decline
decline = {k: ((per_capita_1860[k] - per_capita_1840[k]) / per_capita_1840[k]) * 100 for k in production_1840}

print("Per capita production decline (1860 vs. 1840):", decline)

This code calculates the percentage decrease in per capita production of wheat, pork, and beef between 1840 and 1860.
